July 28, 2017

























Close

























































































        
        Stephen Hasker
    



Dec 16, 2015





























































































Nielsen has promoted Stephen Hasker to global president and chief operating officer, effective Jan. 1. Hasker, who has been global president since August 2014, replaces Brian West, who earlier announced his resignation effective Dec. 31.Hasker will keep his existing responsibilities for Nielsen’s U.S. media business and oversight of its consumer and media product teams. He’ll add responsibility for the company’s Watch and Buy segments globally. The Watch division includes the company’s audio measurement products.
“Steve has made significant and crucial contributions to our business—the most recent of which is his stewardship of our Total Audience framework,” Mitch Barns, CEO, Nielsen said in a news release. “His ability to look across a landscape and understand not only the complexity but also the opportunity is key to our business and that of our clients.”Hasker’s annual salary remains at $900,000, according to an SEC filing, with a $1.1 million bonus subject to meeting certain performance goals. In February 2016, he’ll receive performance-based restricted stock units with a value of $1.5 million.
Before being appointed global president, Hasker was president, Global Product Leadership since February 2013. He joined Nielsen in November 2009 as president, Global Media Products and Advertiser Solutions from McKinsey & Company, where he was a partner in its global media, entertainment and information practice.










































































                
                THE LATEST PEOPLE MOVES
                
            

















People Moves







        

        
        Frank O. Pinion




10 hrs ago




John Craddock, known on the air in St. Louis as “Frank O. Pinion,” is leaving St. Louis Sports Radio “The Big 550 AM” KTRS after more than 20 years with the station. His “Large Morning Show in the Afternoon” program will air its final episode on Sept. 14, according to KTVI-TV.


















People Moves







        

        
        JT Bosch




12 hrs ago




JT Bosch has been named assistant program director and PM drive host for "96.9 The Kat", WKKT, in Charlotte, NC, effective August 14th. Bosch most recently served as APD and evening host for 98.7 WMZQ in Washington, D.C. He also has on air and programming experience for stations in Pennsylvania and Texas.


















People Moves







        

        
        Vince Coglianese



Updated Jul 27, 2017





Cumulus Media news/talk WMAL-AM/FM (630/105.9) Washington, DC has named Vince Coglianese co-host for “Mornings on The Mall.” Coglianese, who is teamed with Mary Walter, replaces Brian Wilson who exited in May. He is the former editor-in-chief of “The Daily Caller,” where he currently serves as editorial director. Coglianese regularly appears on the FOX News Channel, CNN, MSNBC, the FOX Business Network, and CNBC.





































